\f0\b\fs64 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Architectural Concept Note: Automated Photo Identification and Classification for Traffic Violations Using Computer Vision
\f1\fs48 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf2 \strokec2 Executive Overview and Contextual Architecture
\f1\fs36 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 Bengaluru, globally recognized as the "Silicon Valley of India," faces a compounding infrastructural crisis driven by rapid economic expansion and a vehicle population that now exceeds 10 million
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 1
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . While the annual population growth rate of the city stands at 3.7%, the growth rate of registered vehicles accelerates at approximately 10%, culminating in a total of over 1.25 crore vehicles navigating a constrained road network of nearly 14,000 kilometers
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 2
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . To manage this immense volume, the Bengaluru Traffic Police (BTP) has historically relied on initiatives like the B-TRAC project, which utilized a Rs. 217 crore budget to establish the Traffic Management Centre (TMC) on Infantry Road and deploy centrally controlled signaling systems
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 3
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . Subsequent implementations of Intelligent Traffic Management Systems (ITMS) have achieved notable successes, such as issuing over 50 lakh challans and recovering approximately Rs. 38 crores in fines through automated red-light and speed violation detection
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 6
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . However, the sheer scale of the ingested traffic data has exposed a critical operational bottleneck: manual review fatigue.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 Traditional enforcement mechanisms require operators at the TMC to manually verify incidents captured by cameras across the city
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 3
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . Camera hardware inevitably captures degraded imagery due to nighttime conditions, heavy monsoon rains, or erratic vehicle positioning
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 7
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . When automated Automatic Number Plate Recognition (ANPR) systems misread a license plate\'97such as confusing the registration of a CB300R motorcycle with an Access 125 scooter due to a single character error\'97it triggers a chain reaction of manual appeals, email correspondence from aggrieved citizens, and intensive human intervention
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 8
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . The core pain point for the BTP is not a lack of data, but the cognitive load required to process it. The primary objective of an advanced computer vision architecture is not merely to draw bounding boxes around vehicles, but to execute straight-through processing (STP) that eliminates human validation for the vast majority of generated traffic challans.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 To achieve this in the context of the Flipkart Gridlock Hackathon 2.0, the proposed architecture adopts a "Sponsor-First" methodology, directly addressing the manual review fatigue placed on BTP operators. Furthermore, the frontend execution utilizes the "AA Method" (Tangible Visuals), transforming complex tensor operations, optical character extraction, and vector embeddings into a highly interactive, intuitive React.js dashboard designed specifically for non-technical law enforcement personnel. The backend operates on an advanced, edge-deployed stack comprising PyTorch for deep learning inference, OpenCV for deterministic geometric transformations, LangChain and TimescaleDB-backed Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) for temporal analytics, and Kubernetes over AWS Wavelength for scalable, ultra-low-latency deployment
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 9
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 The following sections detail three highly innovative architectural features designed to demonstrate immense technical depth for the engineering review while prioritizing direct operational usability for the Bengaluru Traffic Police.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 \strokec2 Feature 1: "Lumina-FDA" \'97 Zero-Reference Environmental Adaptation Engine
\f1\fs36 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 The Concept
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 Standard Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and object detection models degrade catastrophically under adverse weather conditions such as rain and fog, or in low-light environments, which are highly prevalent in Bengaluru during the monsoon season and nighttime hours. "Lumina-FDA" is a unified preprocessing pipeline that mathematically restores severely degraded video frames in real-time before they reach the primary violation-detection network. The architecture bypasses traditional, computationally heavy image enhancement techniques by combining two cutting-edge PyTorch-based neural architectures: Zero-Reference Deep Curve Estimation (Zero-DCE) for low-light enhancement
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 12
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2  and Fourier Domain Adaptation (FDA) for weather mitigation
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 7
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 Zero-DCE formulates low-light image enhancement as an image-specific curve estimation task, utilizing a lightweight neural network to directly map an input image to an enhanced output at the pixel level
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 16
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . Unlike traditional methods that require paired ground-truth reference images for training, Zero-DCE operates without reference images, making it exceptionally fast and suitable for real-time video processing
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 14
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . The ultra-light backbone uses minimal convolutions\'97some implementations utilizing as few as 58 weights\'97to produce a compact enhancement tensor
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 17
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . Simultaneously, FDA addresses domain shifts caused by rain or fog by computing the Fast Fourier Transform (FFT) of the input image
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 7
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . It swaps the low-frequency amplitude components of the adverse weather image (which contain the visual "style" of the weather) with those of a clear target domain, while preserving the high-frequency phase components that contain the geometric "content" (such as the edges of vehicles and pedestrians)
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 7
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 How it Solves the Sponsor's Pain Point
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 The leading cause of manual review fatigue at the BTP TMC is the "squint factor." Operators are routinely forced to manually enhance, brighten, or zoom into blurry, dark, or foggy CCTV frames to legally verify a license plate, the absence of a seatbelt, or a helmet violation before officially issuing a challan. By autonomously neutralizing environmental variables, the Lumina-FDA pipeline ensures that the downstream vision models\'97and the human operators overseeing them\'97only interact with daylight-equivalent, crystal-clear frames. This drastically reduces the false-negative rate of the detection models and eliminates the countless hours operators currently spend manually discarding "unreadable" or "blurry" footage.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 The Visual/Frontend Component
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 During a fast-paced three-minute hackathon demonstration, translating deep mathematical transformations into a tangible user experience is critical. This feature will be presented on the React.js dashboard as the "Night-to-Day Slider."
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 The dashboard will feature a prominent video feed utilizing a customized react-compare-slider component. As the demonstration begins, the interface will display a heavily degraded, pitch-black, and rain-distorted traffic feed from a BTP camera. The system will intentionally show the raw YOLOv12 model failing to detect any vehicles or violations. The presenter will then drag the vertical slider across the React canvas from right to left. As the slider moves, the exact same video feed will instantly render as a brightly lit, perfectly clear scene. Neon bounding boxes will immediately snap onto helmets, seatbelts, and license plates. A real-time telemetry widget built with the recharts library will display the frames-per-second (FPS) remaining stable at 30+ FPS, proving to the engineering judges that the Zero-DCE/FDA pipeline adds near-zero latency overhead to the inference loop.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 High-Level Execution
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 The execution of the Lumina-FDA pipeline relies on a tightly coupled integration of OpenCV and PyTorch.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Frame Ingestion & Triage:
\f2\b0  OpenCV captures the raw RTSP video stream. A lightweight heuristic checks the global pixel intensity and edge variance. If the intensity falls below a predefined threshold, or if the variance indicates atmospheric scattering (fog/rain), the frame is converted to a PyTorch tensor and routed to the Lumina-FDA pipeline.\cf0 \strokec3 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Low-Light Enhancement (Zero-DCE):
\f2\b0  The tensor is passed through the Zero-DCE CNN. PyTorch applies the estimated spatial curves pixel-wise to dynamically adjust the dynamic range, illuminating the dark regions without overexposing already bright areas such as streetlights or headlights
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 14
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .\cf0 \strokec3 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Weather Mitigation (FDA):
\f2\b0  The PyTorch torch.fft.fftn function computes the 2D discrete Fourier transform of the frame. The central low-frequency amplitudes are attenuated and mapped closer to a clear-weather prior distribution
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 7
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .\cf0 \strokec3 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Inverse Transform:
\f2\b0  An Inverse Fast Fourier Transform (IFFT) reconstitutes the spatial image
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 7
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .\cf0 \strokec3 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Handoff:
\f2\b0  The restored tensor is converted back to an OpenCV format and handed to the primary object detection network.\cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 The quantitative impact of such domain adaptation is substantial, as demonstrated in benchmark studies utilizing FDA on adverse weather datasets.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
