\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 \strokec2 Feature 3: "Chronos-RAG" \'97 Temporal Conversational Analytics & Auto-Ticketing Agent
\f1\fs36 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 The Concept
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 Traditional traffic management dashboards force operators to manually filter through date ranges, vehicle classes, and violation types using rigid drop-down menus to compile end-of-day analytics or file legal First Information Reports (FIRs)
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 32
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . "Chronos-RAG" revolutionizes this by leveraging a state-of-the-art Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) architecture tailored specifically for time-series events. It utilizes LangChain, OpenAI or local Large Language Models (LLMs), and PostgreSQL augmented with the pgvector and TimescaleDB extensions
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 11
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 Every time the Omni-Gaze pipeline detects a violation, the metadata\'97including the timestamp, location coordinates, violation type, vehicle ID, extracted text, and bounding box arrays\'97is embedded as a vector and stored in TimescaleDB
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 11
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . While standard vector databases struggle with chronological filtering, TimescaleDB partitions this vector data by time (hypertables), solving the massive performance bottleneck associated with querying sequential events
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 11
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . A LangChain SQL Agent equipped with tool-calling capabilities is deployed on top of this database, enabling natural language interactions with structured traffic data
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 37
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 How it Solves the Sponsor's Pain Point
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 The manual drafting of daily reports, legal notices, and compliance analytics consumes a vast portion of a BTP officer's shift. Chronos-RAG transitions the TMC system from a tedious "click-and-search" paradigm to a fluid "conversational command" paradigm. If a senior officer requests a report on the effectiveness of a new traffic initiative (e.g., assessing if wrong-side driving decreased after installing new signage), the operator does not need to export CSVs or build pivot tables. They simply ask the system in plain English or Kannada. Furthermore, the LLM autonomously drafts legally sound e-challan descriptions based on the extracted vision data, completely removing the operator's data-entry burden and streamlining the postal or SMS notification workflow
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 25
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 The Visual/Frontend Component
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 This feature will be demonstrated via the "Traffic-GPT Overlay" on the React application.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 On the dashboard, a sleek chat interface persists on the right-hand side of the screen. The presenter will type a complex natural language query into the chat box, such as:
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\i\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 "Show me a breakdown of all wrong-side driving and helmet violations at the Infantry Road junction between 8 AM and 10 AM today, and compare it to the same time window last Tuesday."
\f3\i0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 The frontend will stream the LLM's thought process via WebSockets, creating an engaging live experience. Within seconds, the chat interface will not only reply with a textual summary but will dynamically render a Recharts bar graph directly inside the chat window, illustrating the data.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 To demonstrate the auto-ticketing feature, the presenter will click on a specific violation data point from the graph. The LLM will instantly generate a ready-to-mail legal notice: 
\f5\i "Notice: Vehicle KA-01-AB-9999 was recorded at 08:14 AM on Infantry Road committing a Section 119/177 MV Act violation (Wrong Side Driving). Photographic evidence attached."
\f2\i0  The presenter will then click a single "Approve & Dispatch" button, demonstrating the end-to-end automation of the e-challan generation workflow, proving that the system can immediately interface with the state's postal or SMS APIs
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 6
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 High-Level Execution
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 The execution of Chronos-RAG involves seamlessly connecting vision outputs to database storage and LLM retrieval logic.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Data Ingestion & Embedding:
\f2\b0  The JSON output from the YOLO/OpenCV pipeline is parsed. A unique identifier is generated based on the specific incident timestamp using TimescaleDB's uuid_from_time function
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 11
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . The text metadata is passed through an embedding model and stored in the pgvector columns alongside standard relational data.\cf0 \strokec3 \
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 LangChain SQL Agent Orchestration:
\f2\b0  When a user submits a natural language query, the LangChain create_sql_agent is invoked
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 37
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . The LLM analyzes the prompt and utilizes injected database tools (e.g., sql_db_list_tables, sql_db_schema) to construct a valid, syntactically correct PostgreSQL query
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 38
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .\cf0 \strokec3 \
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Temporal Vector Search:
\f2\b0  For queries requiring semantic matching within a specific time frame, the LangChain agent constructs a query that filters the TimescaleDB partitions by the datetime range 
\f5\i before
\f2\i0  executing the K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN) vector similarity search. This three-step process\'97filtering partitions, performing similarity search, and combining results\'97ensures ultra-fast retrieval even across millions of records
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 11
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .\cf0 \strokec3 \
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Response Generation & Formatting:
\f2\b0  The database returns the structured data. The LLM synthesizes this into a natural language response or formats it as JSON chart data. A FastAPI backend streams this payload to the React.js client asynchronously
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 34
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .\cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 The integration of TimescaleDB offers significant advantages over standard vector databases for traffic law enforcement applications, where time is the most critical axis of measurement.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
