\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 \strokec2 Scalability and Edge Deployment Infrastructure
\f1\fs36 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 To ensure these highly complex computer vision and LLM pipelines can operate in a live production environment handling thousands of camera feeds across Bengaluru without crashing, the architecture mandates a robust, distributed infrastructure. Processing high-resolution video streams requires specialized deployment strategies to prevent bandwidth saturation and ensure ultra-low-latency inference.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 AWS Wavelength and Edge Inference
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 Sending raw 4K video streams from the 14,000 kilometers of Bengaluru roads directly to a centralized cloud server would saturate municipal bandwidth and introduce massive latency, rendering real-time violation detection impossible
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 2
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . The solution utilizes AWS Wavelength and Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service (EKS)
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 9
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 AWS Wavelength brings AWS compute and storage services to the edge of communication service providers' 5G networks
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 9
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . By deploying the PyTorch YOLOv12 and Lumina-FDA models on EKS nodes located within these Wavelength Zones, the video feed is processed mere milliseconds from the physical traffic camera, acting as a Multi-access Edge Computing (MEC) site
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 10
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . The data from the cameras reaches the application servers without ever leaving the telecommunications network, avoiding multiple internet hops
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 9
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . Once the local inference detects an incident, only the lightweight metadata\'97the JSON payload of the violation details and the highly compressed, cropped image of the license plate\'97is transmitted back over secure tunnels to the central AWS Region for long-term storage in TimescaleDB
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 42
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . This paradigm shift from centralized processing to edge processing is critical for scaling the system city-wide.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 Asynchronous Task Queues with Celery and Redis
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 To ensure the React.js frontend remains completely non-blocking and highly responsive for the TMC operators, all heavy post-processing tasks are decoupled from the main application thread. The system utilizes FastAPI to provide asynchronous request handling, which serves as the primary gateway between the frontend and the backend
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 34
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 When a complex operation is required\'97such as executing the TrOCR inference on a difficult license plate or running an extensive LangChain database query for analytics\'97FastAPI pushes the task to a Redis message broker
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 34
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . Celery workers, running on isolated Kubernetes pods, pick up these tasks from the Redis queue, execute the necessary computations, and return the results
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 34
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 . This architecture guarantees that sudden spikes in traffic violations (e.g., during peak rush hour) do not degrade the performance of the dashboard. The Kubernetes Horizontal Pod Autoscaler can dynamically spin up additional Celery worker pods to handle increased loads, isolating the query-serving infrastructure from the data ingestion pipelines
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 34
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 .
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf2 \strokec2 Comprehensive Metric Observability
\f1\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 To maintain the health and legal integrity of the system, comprehensive observability tools are mandatory. Prometheus and Grafana are deployed within the Kubernetes cluster to continuously monitor critical telemetry. This includes tracking hardware utilization across the GPU edge nodes, monitoring YOLOv12 inference times to ensure they remain within the target threshold of single-digit milliseconds
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 9
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2 , and tracking OCR character error rates. If the system detects a spike in OCR failures at a specific junction, it can automatically alert the maintenance crew that a camera lens may require physical cleaning, ensuring the continuous operational readiness of the BTP's enforcement network.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 \strokec2 Strategic Conclusion
\f1\fs36 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 The "Automated Photo Identification and Classification" system outlined in this architectural concept note transcends standard tutorial-level computer vision scripts by addressing the harsh realities of urban traffic management in India. By deeply integrating Lumina-FDA for unprecedented weather and lighting resilience, Omni-Gaze for mathematically robust perspective correction and multi-class relational mapping, and Chronos-RAG for conversational, temporal analytics, the architecture systematically dismantles the core operational bottlenecks of the Bengaluru Traffic Police.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa340\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 This infrastructure is not merely a bounding-box detection tool; it is a comprehensive, edge-deployed automation engine designed to operate securely and efficiently across a massive metropolis. By utilizing AWS Wavelength for zero-latency processing and translating deep learning tensors into an interactive, highly visual React.js interface, this solution guarantees a monumental reduction in manual review fatigue for the TMC operators. The architecture promises to dramatically accelerate the issuance of verifiable, dispute-free e-challans, thereby enforcing traffic discipline, increasing municipal revenue collection, and advancing the fundamental safety of Bengaluru's roadways for its citizens.
\f3\fs24 \cf0 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa340\partightenfactor0

